ul.li: 0 to 1023: Well-known ports. These are typically reserved for system or well-known services (like HTTP on port 80, HTTPS on port 443, etc.).
1024 to 49151: Registered ports. These can be used for non-standard services or user applications. But are often not used for client source ports.
49152 to 65535: Dynamic or private ports (ephemeral ports). These are typically used for client source ports.
